=== Stratified by Stone Size ===
Small stones: A=93.1% vs B=86.7%  (A wins by +6.4%)
Large stones: A=73.0% vs B=68.8%  (A wins by +4.3%)

=== Aggregate (ignoring stone size) ===
A=78.0% vs B=82.6%  (B wins!)

=== The Confounder ===
A treats 263/350 = 75% large stones (harder cases)
B treats 80/350 = 23% large stones
Doctors assigned the more aggressive treatment to harder cases.
Stone size confounds the treatment-outcome relationship.
